# Mobile i18n — all locales required

When adding or changing any user-facing string under `mobile/`, update **every** locale file in `mobile/lib/i18n/`:

`en`, `pl`, `de`, `fr`, `es`, `it`, `cs`, `ru`, `uk`, `be`

## Rules

- Never ship a key only in `pl.json` / `en.json`.
- Do **not** leave English placeholders in non-English locales when neighboring keys in that file are already translated.
- Keep the same key path and interpolation (`{{count}}`, etc.) across all files.
- For count plurals, add the forms that locale needs (e.g. PL/CS/RU/UK/BE: `_one` / `_few` / `_many` / `_other`; EN/DE/FR/ES/IT: usually `_one` / `_other`).
- Before finishing: confirm the new key exists in all 10 JSON files (quick scan or script).

## Example

```text
❌ Added list.filterAll only to pl.json
✅ Added list.filterAll to en + pl + de + fr + es + it + cs + ru + uk + be
   with proper translations in each language
```
